.TH "find_slots" 9 "find_slots" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
find_slots \- Find a place to write the given message.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" find_slots
.BI "(struct tcs_group *tcs "  ","
.BI "const struct tcs_request *msg "  ","
.BI "int *tcs_id "  ","
.BI "int *cmd_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tcs" 12
The tcs group to search.
.IP "msg" 12
The message we want to find room for.
.IP "tcs_id" 12
If we return 0 from the function, we return the global ID of the
TCS to write to here.
.IP "cmd_id" 12
If we return 0 from the function, we return the index of
the command array of the returned TCS where the client should
start writing the message.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only for use on sleep/wake TCSes since those are the only ones we maintain
tcs->slots for.
.SH "RETURN"
-ENOMEM if there was no room, else 0.
